Wiktionary
----------
Every morphology bundle's `lemma` and `form` tables, plus every
realization row in `linguistics-v3.db`, derives from kaikki.org's
machine-readable Wiktionary extracts.

  Source: https://kaikki.org/
  Upstream: https://www.wiktionary.org/
  License: CC BY-SA 4.0
           https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

wordfreq
--------
Every morphology bundle's `freq_rank` column (except Latin) is
assigned by sorting lemmas via Robyn Speer's wordfreq package, which
itself draws on Wikipedia, OpenSubtitles, Twitter samples, Reddit,
news crawls, and the Google Books Ngrams corpus.

  Source: https://github.com/rspeer/wordfreq
  License: MIT
           https://github.com/rspeer/wordfreq/blob/master/LICENSE.txt

Whitaker's WORDS
----------------
The Latin morphology bundle's `freq_rank` column derives from the
8-tier frequency scale embedded in William Whitaker's Latin
dictionary.

  Source: https://mk270.github.io/whitakers-words/
  License: Public domain

